channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: GPT-4 Technical Report
item.description: We report the development of GPT-4, a large-scale, multimodal model which can accept image and text inputs and produce text outputs.

item.title: AdPE: Adversarial Positional Embeddings for Pretraining Vision Transformers via MAE+
item.description: A criterion in unsupervised pretraining is the pretext task needs to be sufficiently hard to prevent the transformer encoder from learning trivial low-level features not generalizable well to downstream tasks.

item.title: Automated Self-Supervised Learning for Recommendation
item.description: This does not generalize across different datasets and downstream recommendation tasks, which is difficult to be adaptive for data augmentation and robust to noise perturbation.

item.title: Diversity-Aware Meta Visual Prompting
item.description: We present Diversity-Aware Meta Visual Prompting~(DAM-VP), an efficient and effective prompting method for transferring pre-trained models to downstream tasks with frozen backbone.

item.title: A CNN Based Framework for Unistroke Numeral Recognition in Air-Writing
item.description: Air-writing refers to virtually writing linguistic characters through hand gestures in three-dimensional space with six degrees of freedom.

item.title: Alias-Free Convnets: Fractional Shift Invariance via Polynomial Activations
item.description: Although CNNs are believed to be invariant to translations, recent works have shown this is not the case, due to aliasing effects that stem from downsampling layers.

item.title: Calibrated Teacher for Sparsely Annotated Object Detection
item.description: Recent works on sparsely annotated object detection alleviate this problem by generating pseudo labels for the missing annotations.

item.title: Automated Ensemble Search Framework for Semantic Segmentation Using Medical Imaging Labels
item.description: Reliable classification and detection of certain medical conditions, in images, with state-of-the-art semantic segmentation networks, require vast amounts of pixel-wise annotation.

item.title: Editing Implicit Assumptions in Text-to-Image Diffusion Models
item.description: Our Text-to-Image Model Editing method, TIME for short, receives a pair of inputs: a "source" under-specified prompt for which the model makes an implicit assumption (e. g., "a pack of roses"), and a "destination" prompt that describes the same setting, but with a specified desired attribute (e. g., "a pack of blue roses").

item.title: V2V4Real: A Real-world Large-scale Dataset for Vehicle-to-Vehicle Cooperative Perception
item.description: To facilitate the development of cooperative perception, we present V2V4Real, the first large-scale real-world multi-modal dataset for V2V perception.

item.title: Co-Salient Object Detection with Co-Representation Purification
item.description: Such irrelevant information in the co-representation interferes with its locating of co-salient objects.

item.title: InstMove: Instance Motion for Object-centric Video Segmentation
item.description: A common solution is to use optical flow to provide motion information, but essentially it only considers pixel-level motion, which still relies on appearance similarity and hence is often inaccurate under occlusion and fast movement.

item.title: DBSCAN of Multi-Slice Clustering for three-order Tensor
item.description: Several methods for triclustering three-dimensional data require the cluster size or the number of clusters in each dimension to be specified.

item.title: Quaternion Orthogonal Transformer for Facial Expression Recognition in the Wild
item.description: Firstly, to reduce redundancy among features extracted from pre-trained ResNet-50, we use the orthogonal loss to decompose and compact these features into three sets of orthogonal sub-features.

item.title: Sr-init: An interpretable layer pruning method
item.description: Our SR-init method is inspired by the discovery that the accuracy drop due to stochastic re-initialization of layer parameters differs in various layers.

item.title: Implicit Stacked Autoregressive Model for Video Prediction
item.description: Future frame prediction has been approached through two primary methods: autoregressive and non-autoregressive.

item.title: On the Implicit Geometry of Cross-Entropy Parameterizations for Label-Imbalanced Data
item.description: Aiming to extend this theory to non-linear models, we investigate the implicit geometry of classifiers and embeddings that are learned by different CE parameterizations.

item.title: Optimizing Deep Learning Model Parameters with the Bees Algorithm for Improved Medical Text Classification
item.description: This paper introduces a novel mechanism to obtain the optimal parameters of a deep learning model using the Bees Algorithm, which is a recent promising swarm intelligence algorithm.

item.title: Window-Based Early-Exit Cascades for Uncertainty Estimation: When Deep Ensembles are More Efficient than Single Models
item.description: Experiments on ImageNet-scale data across a number of network architectures and uncertainty tasks show that the proposed window-based early-exit approach is able to achieve a superior uncertainty-computation trade-off compared to scaling single models.

item.title: On the Connection between Concept Drift and Uncertainty in Industrial Artificial Intelligence
item.description: AI-based digital twins are at the leading edge of the Industry 4. 0 revolution, which are technologically empowered by the Internet of Things and real-time data analysis.

item.title: CB2: Collaborative Natural Language Interaction Research Platform
item.description: CB2 is a multi-agent platform to study collaborative natural language interaction in a grounded task-oriented scenario.

item.title: Parameter is Not All You Need: Starting from Non-Parametric Networks for 3D Point Cloud Analysis
item.description: We present a Non-parametric Network for 3D point cloud analysis, Point-NN, which consists of purely non-learnable components: farthest point sampling (FPS), k-nearest neighbors (k-NN), and pooling operations, with trigonometric functions.

item.title: Implant Global and Local Hierarchy Information to Sequence based Code Representation Models
item.description: Furthermore, we propose the Hierarchy Transformer (HiT), a simple but effective sequence model to incorporate the complete hierarchical embeddings of source code into a Transformer model.

item.title: PiMAE: Point Cloud and Image Interactive Masked Autoencoders for 3D Object Detection
item.description: Masked Autoencoders learn strong visual representations and achieve state-of-the-art results in several independent modalities, yet very few works have addressed their capabilities in multi-modality settings.

item.title: Evaluation of ChatGPT as a Question Answering System for Answering Complex Questions
item.description: As ChatGPT covers resources such as Wikipedia and supports natural language question answering, it has garnered attention as a potential replacement for traditional knowledge based question answering (KBQA) models.

item.title: The Life Cycle of Knowledge in Big Language Models: A Survey
item.description: Knowledge plays a critical role in artificial intelligence.

item.title: A Contrastive Knowledge Transfer Framework for Model Compression and Transfer Learning
item.description: Knowledge Transfer (KT) achieves competitive performance and is widely used for image classification tasks in model compression and transfer learning.

item.title: Sequential three-way decisions with a single hidden layer feedforward neural network
item.description: The experimental results verify that STWD-SFNN has a more compact network on structured datasets than other SFNN models, and has better generalization performance than the competitive models.

item.title: Eliciting Latent Predictions from Transformers with the Tuned Lens
item.description: We analyze transformers from the perspective of iterative inference, seeking to understand how model predictions are refined layer by layer.

item.title: Multiway clustering of 3-order tensor via affinity matrix
item.description: We propose a new method of multiway clustering for 3-order tensors via affinity matrix (MCAM).

item.title: Relational Multi-Task Learning: Modeling Relations between Data and Tasks
item.description: Here we introduce a novel relational multi-task learning setting where we leverage data point labels from auxiliary tasks to make more accurate predictions on the new task.

item.title: Practically Solving LPN in High Noise Regimes Faster Using Neural Networks
item.description: For some settings we are also able to provide theories that explain the rationale of the design of our models.

item.title: Image Label based Semantic Segmentation Framework using Object Perimeters
item.description: Our new PerimeterFit module will be applied to pre-refine the CAM predictions before using the pixel-similarity-based network.

item.title: LayoutDM: Discrete Diffusion Model for Controllable Layout Generation
item.description: Controllable layout generation aims at synthesizing plausible arrangement of element bounding boxes with optional constraints, such as type or position of a specific element.

item.title: DynaMask: Dynamic Mask Selection for Instance Segmentation
item.description: The representative instance segmentation methods mostly segment different object instances with a mask of the fixed resolution, e. g., 28*28 grid.

item.title: SimFLE: Simple Facial Landmark Encoding for Self-Supervised Facial Expression Recognition in the Wild
item.description: One of the key issues in facial expression recognition in the wild (FER-W) is that curating large-scale labeled facial images is challenging due to the inherent complexity and ambiguity of facial images.

item.title: A Simple Framework for Open-Vocabulary Segmentation and Detection
item.description: We present \ourmodel{}, a simple Open-vocabulary Segmentation and Detection framework that jointly learns from different segmentation and detection datasets.

item.title: Blind Video Deflickering by Neural Filtering with a Flawed Atlas
item.description: Prior work usually requires specific guidance such as the flickering frequency, manual annotations, or extra consistent videos to remove the flicker.

item.title: Differential voltage analysis for battery manufacturing process control
item.description: This work highlights the opportunities for leveraging voltage-based electrochemical metrics for online battery manufacturing process control.

item.title: FireRisk: A Remote Sensing Dataset for Fire Risk Assessment with Benchmarks Using Supervised and Self-supervised Learning
item.description: Inspired by the abundance of publicly available remote sensing projects and the burgeoning development of deep learning in computer vision, our research focuses on assessing fire risk using remote sensing imagery.

item.title: The NPU-Elevoc Personalized Speech Enhancement System for ICASSP2023 DNS Challenge
item.description: This paper describes our NPU-Elevoc personalized speech enhancement system (NAPSE) for the 5th Deep Noise Suppression Challenge at ICASSP 2023.

item.title: Reference-Guided Large-Scale Face Inpainting with Identity and Texture Control
item.description: To introduce strong control for face inpainting, we propose a novel reference-guided face inpainting method that fills the large-scale missing region with identity and texture control guided by a reference face image.

item.title: Learning Distortion Invariant Representation for Image Restoration from A Causality Perspective
item.description: In this paper, we are the first to propose a novel training strategy for image restoration from the causality perspective, to improve the generalization ability of DNNs for unknown degradations.

item.title: Unsupervised Representation Learning in Partially Observable Atari Games
item.description: Contrastive methods have performed better than generative models in previous state representation learning research.

item.title: Multi PILOT: Learned Feasible Multiple Acquisition Trajectories for Dynamic MRI
item.description: Several studies have particularly focused on applying deep learning techniques to learn these acquisition trajectories in order to attain better image reconstruction, rather than using some predefined set of trajectories.

item.title: Domain Generalization via Nuclear Norm Regularization
item.description: In this paper, we propose a simple and effective regularization method based on the nuclear norm of the learned features for domain generalization.

item.title: Revisiting Class-Incremental Learning with Pre-Trained Models: Generalizability and Adaptivity are All You Need
item.description: ADAM is a general framework that can be orthogonally combined with any parameter-efficient tuning method, which holds the advantages of PTM's generalizability and adapted model's adaptivity.

item.title: Lite DETR : An Interleaved Multi-Scale Encoder for Efficient DETR
item.description: Recent DEtection TRansformer-based (DETR) models have obtained remarkable performance.

item.title: Erasing Concepts from Diffusion Models
item.description: We propose a fine-tuning method that can erase a visual concept from a pre-trained diffusion model, given only the name of the style and using negative guidance as a teacher.

item.title: Learning Reduced-Order Models for Cardiovascular Simulations with Graph Neural Networks
item.description: Our numerical results demonstrate the accuracy and generalizability of our method in physiological geometries comprising a variety of anatomies and boundary conditions.
